10. Bb3
{ Black is better after this move, but we need to avoid being too hasty – there are some pitfalls. }
10... Nbd7
{ Much better than  10...Nxe4?!  , when  11.Ba3  O-O  12.Re1  Nc5  13.Bxc5  Qxc5  14.Ng5  gives White a nice initiative.  Instead of grabbing material, it is best to improve our piece placement. White's weak pawn structure is a long-term problem, and we don't need to rush the issue. }
11. Be3 Nc5 { Again,  11...Nxe4?  12.Bxf7+  Kxf7  13.Qd5+  should be avoided. }
12. Nd2 O-O
{ Here  12...Nfxe4  13.Nxe4  Nxe4  14.f4  is playable for Black, but White has some compensation for the pawn.  Again, it is much better not to grab material but focus on improving our position. A good plan is ...Be6 next, followed by ...a6-a5-a4,  amongst others. }
