{ That's the issue. We attack the loose bishop but also eye the c3-pawn. } 9.
Qd3 { This looks best. White covers all the weak spots: c3, c4 and e4. } 9...
b5 { White has no way to keep the bishop on the board now. } 10. Bd5 Nxd5 11.
exd5 d6
{ We are happy about Black's chances here. Our structure makes an excellent impression, and White needs to generate enough play to fight for equality. In any case, 7.Bc4 is easy to handle for us. }
