11... h5
{ Here we go! We have firepower against the white kingside, so this attack makes great sense. }
12. Bf1
{ A very sensible move. White secures the bishop and moves a defender to the kingside. }
12... h4 { Alright, this was an easy move. } 13. Bg2 Nc6
{ Our setup is very active and White has to be careful. We think Black has a much easier job in a practical game, but how is the objective evaluation?  It's tough to say, even after a deeper computer analysis. It looks like Black has enough compensation for the pawn, but there are many ways to go wrong at any time. Let's continue and then look at some possible ideas. }
