6. Nge2
{ White develops and prepares kingside castling. This move is quite popular, but it is fairly harmless – as long as we avoid a crucial mistake we already discussed: avoid the early ...d5 push. }
6... Be7
{ We suggest the same approach against the similar move 6.Nh3.  The crucial point is avoiding  6...d5?  , when  7.exd5  exd5  8.Nf4  Nf6  9.Qf3  tears down our position. Delaying the d-pawn is the right choice, keeping our position flexible. }
7. O-O Nc6
{ We play the same setup in the line @@StartFEN@@rn1qkbnr/1b1p1ppp/p3p3/1pp5/4P3/2NP2P1/PPP2PBP/R1BQK1NR w KQkq - 0 6@@EndFEN@@  6.Nh3  Be7  7.O-O  Nc6  , when  8.f4  is the main move and a logical choice for White.  Pushing the f-pawn is also possible here, and our reply @@StartFEN@@r2qk1nr/1b1pbppp/p1n1p3/1pp5/4P3/2NP2P1/PPP1NPBP/R1BQ1RK1 w kq - 4 8@@EndFEN@@  8.f4  h5!  would be the same. It's unnecessary to go any deeper, as the positions are similar. }
8. Be3
{ A solid move, but less ambitious than  8.f4  h5!  , which leads to fun play, quite similar to @@StartFEN@@rn1qkbnr/1b1p1ppp/p3p3/1pp5/4P3/2NP2P1/PPP2PBP/R1BQK1NR w KQkq - 0 6@@EndFEN@@  6.Nh3  Be7  7.O-O  Nc6  8.f4  h5!  . }
8... Nf6 { We develop and get ...Ng4 ideas on the map. } 9. h3
{ White can't do without this move, as ...Ng4 is a constant nuisance. } 9... d6
{ We make sure that e4-e5 is out of the picture and remain flexible in the centre. We can still play the d-pawn to d5 later if desired. In online Blitz games, the following sequence is the most popular. }
10. Qd2 O-O 11. f4 { White finally expands on the kingside. How to react? }
11... d5 { A good moment to strike in the centre. } 12. e5 Nd7
{ The position resembles a French Defence, but there is an important difference compared to the main lines of the French: White's pieces @@StartBracket@@Bg2, Ne2@@EndBracket@@ are passively placed and don't help support the break f4-f5. Without this pawn break, White has a hard time finding a plan.  On the other hand, Black has an automatic attack on the queenside. We can play ...b4, ...a5, sometimes ...Ba6. Black is in good shape here, having the much easier plan. }
