11... d6
{ This is the crucial move to remember! It's critical to recognise the difference to @@StartFEN@@r1bqk1nr/3p1ppp/p3p3/1pb5/4P3/1QN2N2/PP3PPP/R1B1R1K1 w kq - 1 11@@EndFEN@@  11.a4  b4  12.Nd5  , when  12...Ne7  is good.   Here,  11...Ne7?  is bad due to  12.Qc3!  , when White is not in bad shape at all. }
